    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen autoindenting block comments, the second level of the comment always gets auto-indented. For example a jsdoc comment gets autoindented like so:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0c2a78e3-9ca2-4ed1-8176-9b2568ef636a)\r\nThis is with a tabstop of 4.\r\nIt also causes a function or the next line of code to be similarly indented.\r\nAdditional info:\r\n- using the native lsp with lsp-zero on top and relevant language servers when hitting `=` to auto indent\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI would expect block comments to follow in line:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a2297dfd-c160-43e8-ba0b-26ab8fe7bdf9)\r\nI apologise if there is something I'm overlooking here, I haven't found anyone else mentioning it and its quite frustrating when shifting things around after having manually indented block comments to their general form.",
